import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['precipitation'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, alpha=0.5, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['precipitation'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['precipitation'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation in Seattle from 2012 to 2015?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['temp_max'])
    plt.title('How does the maximum temperature vary over time in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Maximum Temperature (F)')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['wind'], data['temp_max'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Wind Speed (mph)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Maximum Temperature (F)')
    ax.axvline(data['wind'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Wind Speed: {:.2f}'.format(data['wind'].mean()))
    ax.axhline(data['temp_max'].mean(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Max Temperature: {:.2f}'.format(data['temp_max'].mean()))
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between wind speed and temperature in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['weather'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the most common weather condition observed in Seattle from 2012 to 2015?', wrap=True)

chart = plot(data)
